gov.nih.nlm.meme.client
Class Version

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.client.Version
public class Version
extends Object

The Version class provides package version information for gov.nih.nlm.meme.client package. History

08/15/2005:
ClientConstants for MIDSVCS_HOST and MIDSVCS_PORT were changed to interact properly with normalized environment implementation.
06/17/2005:
Many updates to method javadoc comments, and some formatting optimizations. MappingClient has additional methods for the viewer/editor application.
03/11/2005:
InsertionClient supports initial recipe step implementation.
01/25/2005:
ActionClient does a better job of reporting transaction/work_ids to the server. (fixes a bug with undo.pl) HTTPRequestClient uses more stable mechanism for talking to server. It attempts to try again upon failures and to reconnect to the server to receive a response if a request got through. This should address most of NLM network issues. MaintenanceClient supports an "exec" call.
01/15/2004:
Improvements to {@link ActionClient} so that it passes work_id of batch actions through to the MBA call. Also passes "force" parameters through to server side. Additionally supports undo/redo of any logged action. Changes to {@link AuxiliaryDataClient} and {@link EditingClient} to use transaction and work log objects instead of ids when requesting activity logs and errors. Improvements to {@link MaintenanceClient}, including support for logging progress, resetting progress, logging operations, running matrix initializer and CUI assignment.
12/13/2004:
{@link AuxiliaryDataClient} has setTermgroup {@link WorklistClient} main method moved to test suite. {@link ActionClient} has getWorkLogsByType and getErrors. {@link MaintenanceClient} supports assigning cuis, executing arbitrary queries, executing arbitrary scripts, and loading tables. {@link AdminClient} supports setSystemStatus.
11/05/2004:
SO_TIMEOUT in {@link HTTPRequestClient} was causing client to have to wait for a long time before figuring out that it could not connect to the server. This settin was removed so that it will fail faster. New {@link MEMERelaEditorKit} method for adding RELA values (to support all fields). Now supported on server side with an action. {@link ActionClient} now provides access to {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.WorkLog} and {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.Activity} objects based on work_id and transaction_id values. {@link ConceptMappingClient} now supports read and write methods. Implements functions on the cui_map table. {@link AuxiliaryDataClient} now supports editing of sources, termgroups, languages, editor preferences, and the semantic type list. {@link EditingClient} now supports all new methods of sub-clients.
09/19/2004:
Improvements/changes to {@link ContentViewClient}. New {@link ConceptMappingClient}. {@link HTTPRequestClient} uses 30 min SO_TIMEOUT. {@link ClientAPI} initiates/terminates sessions with null mid service which should solve the problem with the data source pool overflow.
07/20/2004:
Small bug fix for {@link AdminClient}.getTransactionLog, it should now properly use a data source. {@link ContentViewClient} was updated to have setContentView method.
07/09/2004:
New {@link ContentViewClient} for managing content views. We will build a web application to leverage this.
06/14/2004:
{@link CoreDataClient} has getInverseRelationship {@link EditingClient} updated to reflect new {@link CoreDataClient} method.
05/06/2004:
{@link CoreDataClient}, {@link ReportsClient}, and {@link EditingClient} now support a switch to include or exclude a set of languages (represented as strings) for reading content from the MID.
04/21/2004:
{@link FinderClient} and {@link EditingClient} support restrictByReleasable
04/19/2004:
{@link CoreDataClient} and {@link ReportsClient} now support the reading of non-ENG atoms (by default) and supply a mechanism for toggling between reading/not reading them.
03/17/2004:
{@link EditingClient} was upgraded to correctly support the setting of host/port parameters. {@link HTTPRequestClient} uses a buffered writer for the socket. And RxNormClient works better if the worklist length is 0.
02/06/2004:
{@link MappingClient} now fully implements its API, providing functions for deleting, creating, and editing {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.common.MapSet}s, {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.common.Mapping}s, and {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.common.MapObject}s and their attributes. {@link CoreDataClient} supports richer set of methods for accessing core data, including a method for obtaining only sections of the relationships, instead of the entire amount. It also now supports methods for directly accessing all types of core data.
01/16/2004:
{@link ActionClient} now throws {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.exception.StaleDataException}. {@link MergeEngineClient} has a better progress listener (prints out timestamps). {@link MappingClient} is now fully implemented, with the ability to create edit and delete {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.common.MapSet} information.
12/29/2003:
{@link MappingClient} supports create/delete methods. {@link MergeEngineClient} connects a progress listener and cleans up the log and progress methods a bit.
12/19/2003:
Architecture for passing {@link ClientProgressEvent}s from the server back to the client is now in place. {@link ClientProgressListener} was added. {@link MEMERequestClient} and {@link ClientAPI} now support addClientProgressListener and removeClientProgressListener. {@link ReportsClient} was also updated to handle the new option which allows you to restrict the REVIEWED RELATIONSHIPS view to a particular number of rows (also supported by xreports.pl). {@link ReportsClient} supports the new option to restrict the view of REVIEWED relationships in a concept report. {@link MappingClient} can now provide read access to mappings.
12/15/2003:
Updated javadocs for some clients. {@link HTTPRequestClient} was not totally thread-safe in that it was re-using serializer objects across requests. We simply made these things local variables (which should carry little performance cost) and now multiple threads should be able to simultaneously access the client APIs without problems. {@link ClientAPI} calls setSessionId() now when initiating requests, allowing subclasses to override the method and add functionality to an initiateSession() request. {@link MappingClient} was implemented and provides read access to mappings within the MID.
12/04/2003:
{@link AdminClient}, {@link ChangeServerDialog}, {@link MergeEngineClient}, {@link PrintConceptReportAction}, and RxNormClient have updated javadoc comments. {@link CoreDataClient} provides access to dead data elements. {@link ActionClient} gets passed back more information from the server than before, and comments were updated to reflect the fact that the authority should be set when using this client. {@link EditingClient} was updated to reflect {@link ActionClient} and {@link CoreDataClient} changes.. The {@link ClientAPI} was upgraded to support control over the session timeout and all sub-clients now support the functionality via inheritance (there is a setTimeout method).
11/07/2003:
{@link ActionClient}.processAction(MolecularAction) now sets the molecule_id of the molecular action. {@link PrintConceptReportAction} now strips out the links from reports before printing, to increase printing performance.
10/31/2003:
Fixed {@link TestReportFrame} copy/paste problem. {@link EditingClient} was updated to reflect the various sub-clients that it implements.
10/22/2003:
{@link PrintConceptReportAction} was mistakenly printing only one page per sheet of paper, this was upgraded to 2.
10/16/2003:
{@link TestReportFrame} and {@link PrintConceptReportAction} now are connected to printing API.
09/08/2003:
The {@link ActionClient} main method was improved so that it properly handles errors and returns an error code. This is to allow code like batch.pl to properly catch errors. The client was also extended to attach a violations vector to an action passed to processAction(MolecularAction) so that the client-side can have access to integrity warnings.
08/25/2003:
{@link ChangeServerDialog} changed to prevent duplicates in server list. {@link PrintConceptReportAction} changed to fix formatting of links. {@link TestReportFrame} is now a {@link gov.nih.nlm.swing.GlassPaneListener}. Also, we fixed the refresh bug in {@link PrintConceptReportAction} while the print dialog is open.
08/19/2003:
{@link ActionClient} bug fix, it properly handles the IntegrityViolationException now. Vlad reported a problem with the processAction(MolecularAction) method always reporting an exception (array out of bounds), this fixes the problem. {@link PrintConceptReportAction} properly handles the new non-pre tag HTML concept reports. {@link AdminClient} has a new method for requesting the server switch the default mid service.
08/11/2003:
{@link ActionClient} throws IntegrityViolationException now when processing molecular actions (making it easier for Jekyll to handle it). {@link ReportsClient} now returns {@link gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.ActionReport} objects which encapsulate the data involved in an action, and supports the old-style access via getActionReportDocument().
08/01/2003:
{@link ActionClient}'s main method was updated to support $MEME_HOME/bin/{un,redo.pl. The PrintConceptReportAction and TestReportFrame were updated to support correct printing of the concept reports from Jekyll.
07/16/2003:
TestReportFrame scrolls to top of report explicitly, when any of the setXXX methods are called. TestFinderFrame no longer has synchronized setResults method, this was causing display refresh problems on the sun.
06/27/2003:
Bug fix in ActionClient.
06/06/2003:
ActionClient now sets the relationship_id, attribute_id, or atom_id when inserting this data. It also sets the target id of a MolecularSplitAction and the source id of a MolecularInsertConceptAction. RxNormClient does a slightly better job at handling concept worklists where there are > worklist_size*2 rows in the worklist that comes back (due to CDs being connected to >1 SCD).
06/06/2003:
Minor bug in EditingClient fixed. AuxiliaryDataClient now provides better access to integrity system. AdminClient supports killServer method to kill the server even if other threads are running. ClientToolkit has an additional initialize method that takes a properties object instead of reading from a file. TestFinderFrame given additional logic in main method to support java web start.
05/08/2003:
RxNormClient has better error reporting.
05/08/2003:
MergeEngineClient no longer manages access to its session logs internally, it uses AdminService. RxNormClient was upgraded to support faster worklist reads. AdminClient was upgraded to support access to server logs, session logs, and transacton logs (all with the head/tail API).
04/25/2003:
ActionClient was updated to fix a bug in communicating the target_id back to the application. CoreDataClient was updated to throw MissingDataExceptions from the various getConcept methods, this is so client applications can safely handle this type of error. EditingClient the getCurrentEnglishSource methods where renamed getCurrentEnglishSources. Finally, the RxNormClient was given two additional methods for reading worklists in a parallelized way. All clients were updated to cast exceptions returned by the server to MEMEException instead of to ClientException.
04/09/2003:
CoreDataClient has now a populateContextRelationships method for reading context rels when so desired. Debugging System.out.println statements where cleaned up. RxNormClient now has methods for reading the worklist like an iterator. These methods support making multiple requests to the server to prevent it from timing out, and eventually can be extended to support reading different segments in parallel to maximize performance. ActionClient now feeds-back the target id of molecular actions and correctly populates the target concept (where used).
04/01/2003:
RxNormClient has access to the worklist contents, allowing large worklists to be read without error. EditingClient supports a getCurrentEnglishSources method as does AuxiliaryDataClient. CoreDataClient was reconfigured to provide faster access to core data. Reading a concept now leaves out the relationships, but a populateRelationships method allows rels to be read when needed (also for context relationships).
03/19/2003:
TestReportFrame was given a "Print" button. ActionClient main method was cleaned up to make it easier to call.
03/05/2003:
GUI Actions ChangeServerAction and ChangeDataSourceAction were added to support GUI applications (along with the supporting classes). was updated to serve as an example. ActionClient was extended to support batch and macro actions. MergeEngineClient and ActionClient have main methods that interact cleanly with the new scripts: insert.pl, batch.pl, and merge.pl. This is one part of the effort to migrate completely from MEME3 to MEME4. AuxiliaryDataClient was given a getNextIdentifierForType method for obtaining new transaction ids.
01/13/2003:
The AdminClient and WorklistClient were updated to support action harvester and admin web applications.
11/13/2002:
the FinderClient was upgraded to support action lookups and the ReportsClient was upgraded to support the action harveseter (action and editing reports).
08/28/2002:
Official release of the editing APIs, including: ActionClient, AuxiliaryDataClient CoreDataClient, FinderClient, WorklistClient, and the super-client EditingClient. The EditingClient is intended as a single access point for all MEME editing services. It should serve as an API that supplies all of the needs of a prospective Java MEME editing interface. A small GUI application TestFinderFrame was relased to leverage the APIs. Finally, this is the official first release of the RxNormClient used by the RxNorm editor to edit SCD graphs.
05/13/2002:
MEMERelaEditorKit was upgraded to support actions on relationships spanning concept ids.
04/22/2002:
AuxiliaryDataClient was added. It provides client access to non-core mid data.
03/26/2002:
ReportsClient was extended to support styles. This class now has the full functionality available to $MEME_HOME/bin/xreports.pl.

Also, MEMERelaEditorKit was extended with a insertRelationshipAttribute method that allows it to add RELAs and their inverses to the system.

03/05/2002:
AdminClient was added to consolidate administrative services. LogClient was deprecated and made to just call AdminClient methods. ReportsClient nas an additional method that supports
11/01/2001:
1st Release.

Author:
MEME Group
